				#content : 'I am NeoJSONArray.\rI am an Array.\r\rI am often used in combination with NeoJSONObject, to represent the result of parsing JSON.\r \r I support path access for nested instances of me, using #atPath: and #atPath:put:\r \rUsed in its generic way, NeoJSONParser will return Arrays and Dictionaries.\rReturning NeoJSONArrays and NeoJSONObjects, simple subclasses, allows to add some convenience methods.\r',
